The White House held a conference call with legal experts on May 27, 2009, to discuss the nomination of Judge Sotomayor. The call included Professor Stephen L. Carter from Yale Law School, Paul M. Smith from Jenner & Block, LLP, Professor William P. Marshall from the University of North Carolina School of Law, Professor Martha L. Minow from Harvard Law School, Kevin K. Russell from Howe & Russell, LLP, and Dean Evan H. Caminker from the University of Michigan Law School. The call took place at 2:30 PM EDT, and the dial-in number for the call was (866) 861-5393.